<tt>Fri May  2 20:31:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hey, Doc!  I agree 100%.  When I see the stuff that these guys went through;  it is about time.  I have seen the Korean War Memorial in D.C. (It is in the same general area as the Wall).  It is AWESOME!  It shows a patrol in a paddy.  All covered by ponchos and strung out in a V formation.  The statues are literally larger than life.  They are 8ft. tall.  The detail of the weariness in their faces, their stances(frozen in time), makes you feel the cold and tiredness.  It is difficult to describe the impact of this squad.  But it takes the breathe away.  It happens that nam vets see it and it stops them in their tracks.  Most look, then look again, drawn to the front where they see the faces.  Most turn to see older guys looking and there is a recognition of fellow warriors.  There is a generation gap but it disappears when the Nam vet says to the Korean vet &quot;It's about time.  Welcome Home&quot;.
